spans.text: that unhappy tribe who nought pursue : Who sin , for want of something else to do
And to be blessed indeed , needs only move
What numbers , sloth with gloomy humours
what loud outcries , and well-meaning rage , What endless quarrels at the present age
Such vice ! — well , sure , the last day
The sad creation of distempered brains , Dispatch , dear friend ! move , labour , sweat , run ,
these whenever you see them swell
them cross — poor men ! they are not well
— poor men ! they are not well
still more to interrupt my ease
my devotion still to be employed
Man should be suffered thus to play the fool , To keep from hurt
it's greater trouble , if you do ; And if it's labouring only , men profess , Who writes the hardest , writes with most success
Who writes the hardest , writes with most success
